In general, Azure PaaS only supports Java LTS versions and Azure Spring Cloud will support Java 17 LTS. **The hosting environment contains the latest version of Azul Zulu OpenJDK for Azure**_

/!\ **[IMPORTANT Update](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/developer/java/fundamentals/java-support-on-azure)** June 30th, 2021:\xa0Zulu for Azure will no longer receive updates or support starting January 1st, 2022. Azure services are transitioning to\xa0Microsoft Build of OpenJDK\xa0for JDK 11 .

When Azure Spring Cloud environment  will rely on Microsoft Build of OpenJDK\xa0for JDK 11 ?
Could you please update the doc accordingly ?

'2022-03-22T14:29:33Z', 'updated_at': '2022-03-22T17:41:48Z', 'closed_at': None, 'author_association': 'NONE', 'active_lock_reason': None, 'body': 'In the Azure Portal / Azure Spring Cloud instance / Apps / myApp / Deployment, the create deployment leads to the doc, why it is not possible to create a deployment from the portal ?

Also by default, there is NO deployment at all, even not Production, as a consequence any App deployment through CLI or CI/CD fails whereas the CLI does not state that --deployment is required  

```bash
az spring-cloud app deploy --name admin-server --artifact-path spring-petclinic-admin-server\target\spring-petclinic-admin-server-2.6.3.jar --jvm-options="-Xms2048m -Xmx2048m -Dspring.profiles.active=mysql" -g rg-iac-asc-petclinic-mic-srv --service asc-petcliasc
```
fails with 
```console
No production deployment found, use --deployment to specify deployment or create deployment with: az spring-cloud app deployment create
```

fails with 
```console
Action failed with error: Production deployment does not exist in service asc-*** app MyApp
```

What would be needed as well is a GitHub action task to do the quivalent of 'az spring-cloud app deployment create'

---

Hi, 
good documentation here, however, does not make it clear that the e.g. ${db.url} substitution parameters do not work for a Java/Tomcat in an App Serevice when the context.xml is 'inside the .war' file in the META-INF folder.

Unless there is a way to get this to work?? 
I simply get errors such as 
`"Cannot create JDBC driver of class 'org.gjt.mm.mysql.Driver' for connect URL '${MYSQLCONNSTR_ecommerceDB}'`

The command 

```
az spring-cloud app create --name api-gateway --instance-count 1 --memory 2 --assign-endpoint
az spring-cloud app create --name customers-service --instance-count 1 --memory 2
```

produces a warning 

```
Memory quantity [--memory] should be specified with unit, such as 512Mi, 1Gi. Support for integer quantity will be dropped in future release.
This command usually takes minutes to run. Add '--verbose' parameter if needed.
[1/3] Creating app api-gateway
[2/3] Creating default deployment with name "default"
[3/3] Updating app "api-gateway" (this operation can take a while to complete)
App create succeeded
```

The unit should be set to avoid to the warning

Document intent:
This document describes setting up Azure AD as an Identity Provider for Azure Function Apps under the Authorization/Authentication section. Then selecting Azure AD from a drop down list of identity providers. 

Document issue:
The Azure Function App no longer has a section called "Authorization/Authentication", it only has a section called "Authentication". And when adding an identity provider, there is no longer any Azure AD option available in the drop down. So it appears to be impossible to assign an AAD identity provider to the Azure Function App. This appears to be a breaking change for connecting the Azure Function App as a connector to the corresponding Azure Logic App.


---
